text:
(1) A general view, east from the New York Telephone Building, 140 West Street, from Vesey to Barclay Streets, showing in the background the East River, with the Brooklyn Bridge; at the left, is the Municipal Building, (at Centre and Chambers Streets); and in the centre, the Woolworth Building, (233 Broadway, between Barclay Street and Park Place).

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, from a different angle.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) The same, another view.

P. L. Sperr.

text:
(1) A general view, east from the New York Telephone Building, 140 West Street, from Vesey to Barclay Streets, showing the East River in the background, and in the centre, St. Paul's Protestant Episcopal Chapel and Grounds, (Broadway west to Church Street, and Fulton north to Vesey Streets). August 6, 1930. P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, from a different angle, showing the Woolworth Building, (233 Broadway, between Barclay Street and Park Place), and only a small portion of St. Paul's Protestant Episcopal Chapel and Grounds. August 6, 1930. P. L. Sperr.

text:

P. L. Sperr.
